  • 4 wk) → remodeling (4 wk
  • 1+ yr). Intrinsic healing (tenocytes — maintains glide) vs extrinsic (peritendon — adhesions). Early controlled motion → intrinsic healing + collagen alignment → BETTER outcomes than complete immobilization. Steroid impairs. Continues 6-12 months. Clinical applications: flexor tendon, rotator cuff, Achilles rehab.

